All Classes

Class Description
App
App launches the Ancestry Tool App
CalculatorData
CalculatorData contains Gedmatch calculator data (breakdown / color scheme).
CalculatorInput
CalculatorInput is used to construct a custom calculator input panel
ConfirmPopup
ConfirmPopup is a custom confirmation popup with YES / NO options, extending WarningPopup
DatabaseAccess
DatabaseAccess manages interactions with the local Database
DatabaseAddWindow
DatabaseAddWindow is used to add new samples to database
DatabaseWindow
DatabaseWindow contains main database table and its toolbar
DefaultObjects
DefaultObjects contains customised java swing default object generating methods
Distance
Distance measures a theoretical distance from target to all database source samples.
DistanceData
DistanceData regulates Distance calculator color scheme
DistanceMixed
DistanceMixed is an extension of Distance used to obtain a broadly mixed distance map to a given target.
DistanceWindow
DistanceWindow displays Distance calculator input options and output
LayoutData
LayoutData regulates App layout color schemes
MapData
MapData contains SignalMap regions, region keyword, coordinates and values
MenuWindow
MenuWindow is the main menu window of the App started upon launch
Navigation
Navigation contains various generic GUI methods used by App Windows
Sample
Sample accommodates ancestry sample kit related data (instances) and methods.
SampleAncient
SampleAncient extends SampleModern (and Sample), used for Ancient DNA samples
SampleAverage
SampleAverage extends Sample, refers to several Samples grouped as one.
SampleDataTable
SampleDataTable is a custom JTable extension to display Sample percentage breakdown
SampleModern
SampleModern extends Sample, used for Modern DNA samples
SampleNotFoundException
Thrown there arent any samples matches for given id
SamplePie
SamplePie represents pie chart based on parentSample percentages
SampleTable
SampleTable is a custom JTable extension to display samples
SampleWindow
SampleWindow displays selected sample information, breakdown table and pie chart
SearchList
SearchList is a JPanel extension providing a searchable JComboBox
Signal
Signal refers to individual SignalMap signals.
SignalMap
SignalMap is a world map used to display the regional distribution of the local database with signals.
Single
Single measures what a sample would theoretically consist of based on database source samples.
SingleTable
SingleTable is used to display Single calculator output.
SingleWindow
SingleWindow displays Single calculator input options and output table
SortingNotRecognizedException
Thrown when given sorting type is not recognized
TableData
TableData contains sample table headers and content retrieval methods
UploadWindow
UploadWindow facilitates database uploads
WarningPopup
WarningPopup is a warning popup with custom message
Window
General Window SuperClass for Ancestry Tool App
